last_episode_to_air.name: Race to Ma and Pa
last_episode_to_air.overview: Bo and Jane have a fun family day planned, but when they get trapped trying to help a wild T-Rex in distress, the Jr Ranchers must rescue their parents from a real dino-mergency!

name: Dino Ranch
overview: Dino Ranch follows the adventures of the Cassidy family as they tackle life in a fantastical "pre-westoric" setting where dinosaurs still roam. As the young ranchers learn the ropes, they discover the thrill of ranch life whilst navigating the great outdoors through unpredictable challenges.

episodes.name: Big Jon Big Trouble
episodes.overview: Jon tries to train a rambunctious dino all by himself.

episodes.name: Min's Quest
episodes.overview: When Min overcomes adversity to find an elusive flower, she helps to cure a brontosaurus.

episodes.name: Stop That Spinosaurus!
episodes.overview: When a rampaging dinosaur threatens to cause havoc, thanks to Miguel and his observant nature, Jon learns that sometimes it's better to slow down and think the problem through.

episodes.name: The Spookasaurus
episodes.overview: When Jon gets spooked by a campfire story about a legendary dinosaur, he doesn't want to admit it to Miguel and Min, then eventually comes clean and learns that his family is there for him whether he's scared or not.

episodes.name: Jane's Perfect Present
episodes.overview: After the Jr. Ranchers spend all their time trying to prepare a special surprise birthday gift for Jane, they find out that all she really wanted was to spend the day with them, and learn that spending your time with someone is the best gift of all.

episodes.name: Pterodactyl-Doodle-Doo
episodes.overview: When Miguel's creation of a new roost for Pteddy results in some unintended consequences, Miguel and the Jr. Ranchers learn that taking other people's feelings into consideration is the most important part of any good deed.

episodes.name: The Long Way Home
episodes.overview: Jon learns that shortcuts aren't always shorter when the Ranchers get lost in the badlands with the hungry Thunderfoot on their trail.

episodes.name: Trade in the Shade
episodes.overview: When an uncooperative Brontosaurus gets between the Jr. Ranchers and their goal to harvest the delicious apples from the orchard, the gang discovers the importance of placing others' needs ahead of their own.

episodes.name: Small Wonder
episodes.overview: When a scrappy little compy gets underfoot trying to be just like Blitz, Blitz learns that even the smallest member of the team can make a big difference.

episodes.name: Dino Checkup Hiccup
episodes.overview: After Clover accidentally breaks Min’s stegoscope and tries to hide the evidence, he learns that he should never be afraid to tell Min when he makes a mistake.

episodes.name: Tinhorn Trouble
episodes.overview: When the Tinhorns trick the Dino Ranchers, Min proves that no matter the circumstances, you should always do the right thing and help.

episodes.name: Family Comes First
episodes.overview: Pitted against the Tinhorns on Rancheroo Day, Jon learns that his family is more important to him than winning.

episodes.name: Clover's Tiny Problem
episodes.overview: When Min dotes on a newly hatched dino, Clover feels jealous, but then learns that no dinosaur can replace him in Min’s heart.

episodes.name: Tango's BFF
episodes.overview: After helping a fellow triceratops, Tango becomes attached to her new friend and doesn’t want her to rejoin her herd, but learns that it’s selfish to keep her from her family.

episodes.name: Home on the Range
episodes.overview: When a dinosaur named Wanda keeps running away from the Ranch, Min, Jon and Miguel discover that she’s eager to join to a dinosaur family that wants to welcome her as one of their own – and are reminded that you don’t have to be born into a family to be welcomed into one.

episodes.name: Miguel's Compy Conundrum
episodes.overview: After Miguel accidentally causes the ranch to be overrun with Compys, he learns that working hard to correct a mistake can sometimes yield a surprising result.

episodes.name: The Ten Gallon Trophy
episodes.overview: When Bopper runs off with Bo's prized Ten Gallon Trophy Hat, Tango believes that she has to be like Blitz and Clover in order to help the gang catch the elusive pachyosaur, then learns that she can help the team best by just being herself.

episodes.name: Plane Crazy
episodes.overview: When Miguel underestimates his dino pals and gets carried away by his dream of flying, he learns that he needs to believe in his dino-friends as much as he believes in an idea.

episodes.name: Sneaky Swimpers
episodes.overview: When things begin to disappear from Dino Ranch, Blitz and the gang discover the importance of knowing the facts before jumping to conclusions.

episodes.name: Clover's Height Fright
episodes.overview: When Pteddy gets stuck atop the Mile High Mesa, Clover must overcome his fear of heights by taking things one step at a time to help his friend.

episodes.name: The Ballad of Big Jon
episodes.overview: Prompted by a western hero, Jon wants to prove he's a real epic hero as well, but learns it’s the smaller, more everyday good deeds that really make him a hero to his family.

episodes.name: One Good Turn
episodes.overview: A pack of wild raptors go after Min and Jane as they're transporting a precious brontomelon in the medicine wagon, and in the ensuing chase they discover an act of kindness is often returned with kindness.

episodes.name: Guitar Heroes
episodes.overview: The Ranchers need Ogie Tinhorn's help to return a skittish dinosaur to its family, and Jon learns that even 'bad' guys have 'good' hearts.

episodes.name: Wild Wild Thunderfoot
episodes.overview: The Tinhorns trap Thunderfoot and the Dino Ranchers need to set him free.

episodes.name: Lost Dinosaur
episodes.overview: Min spots a rare dinosaur in a hidden forest but later realizes it's very important to always respect nature.

episodes.name: The Dino Doldrums
episodes.overview: When the Ranch dinos come down with an illness, Blitz learns it's important to admit when he's not feeling well

episodes.name: Goliath's Little Helper
episodes.overview: Clover learns that even though he's not strong enough yet to be a barn builder like his grandpa, his job on the Ranch is just as important.

episodes.name: Have You Herd?
episodes.overview: When a stego finds more joy acting like a compy, Jon learns family can come in all shapes and sizes.

episodes.name: Treasure Ranch
episodes.overview: Miguel and the Ranchers must protect the ranch from the Tinhorns from storming the mine and stop himself from getting caught up in the emerald excitement

episodes.name: Good Neighbors
episodes.overview: Jon learns that being 'neighborly' means helping everyone in need.

episodes.name: Blitz Be Gone
episodes.overview: After avoiding his Dino Dental check-up, Blitz learns that he had nothing to worry about and he's glad that he tried something new.

episodes.name: Little Big Shot
episodes.overview: Miguel invents a mechanical lasso but when it malfunctions he learns to keep trying and never give up.

episodes.name: Pterodackattack!
episodes.overview: When Miguel builds a dam on the creek to create a dino watering hole, the ranch is suddenly marauded by hungry wild pterodactyls snatching up food!

episodes.name: Sonny the Kid
episodes.overview: When the infamous dino rustler Sonny the Kid threatens to ruin her friends big day, Min volunteers to guard the Dino Airport; a task that proves to be easier said than done with all the exciting Opening Day events that keep drawing Min’s attention.

episodes.name: Dino Sore
episodes.overview: Jon injures himself rescuing a wild raptor, and in order to reunite it with its family, he must be willing to play a different role and let Min and Miguel take the lead.

episodes.name: Strife in the Fast Lane
episodes.overview: Min’s excitement to deliver an egg to her friend leads the Dino Ranch gang into a runaway comedy of errors when their hastily repaired egg cart gets away on them.

episodes.name: Ranch-a-Palooza
episodes.overview: When Min puts her chores off to have fun with Tara, it causes a chain of events that leads to Angus squaring off with a wild spinosaurus.

episodes.name: Sky's the Limit
episodes.overview: Jon becomes upset when he doesn’t take to ptero-flying as quickly as Min and Miguel, and pushes himself to be the best when he tries to fly a delivery through powerful winds.

episodes.name: Trading Day
episodes.overview: When the Jr. Ranchers switch up their dino-rides, they have a hard time getting used to each other’s dinosaurs.

episodes.name: It's a Dino Egg-Mergency!
episodes.overview: When a batch of eggs need to be moved from the Hatchery and start hatching, Min spirals into a frenzy trying to wrangle the rambunctious newborns and keep them safe.

episodes.name: This Ranch Ain't Big Enough
episodes.overview: When a sick spinosaurus needs to be tended to at the Ranch, Miguel lies to Biscuit to keep the two giants apart.

episodes.name: Family Feud
episodes.overview: Riding out to lead a herd of triceratops to greener pastures becomes a much more difficult task when the gang won't stop squabbling and pointing fingers.

episodes.name: Stink to High Noon
episodes.overview: When Sonny the Kid hides stink weeds all over the Ranch, Jon goes against Min and Miguel's advice and is goaded into a lasso challenge by the outlaw.

episodes.name: Herds of a Feather
episodes.overview: After a mix-up by Miguel results in a baby T-Rex hatching at the Dino Airport, Miguel seeks to help the little dinosaur find his place among the airport team.

episodes.name: Ridin' Mighty
episodes.overview: While helping Tara make an important delivery, Jon's confidence goes to his head causing care-less mistakes, and he must accept that there's always more a Rancher can learn.

episodes.name: Calling All Riders!
episodes.overview: The Cassidys and Tinhorns face off in a race, but it's only through learning to work together that they're able to finish the race.

episodes.name: Storm-A-Lert
episodes.overview: In the middle of an approaching storm, Miguel rushes through his important jobs so he can work on his new invention, but he needs to make sure one task is finished before he moves on to another.

episodes.name: Adoptasaurus Rex
episodes.overview: Ma and Pa inspire the Ranchers to fight through adversity and give an egg to a pair of T-rexes who can’t have their own.

episodes.name: Dino Ranch Rocks
episodes.overview: The Cassidys’ party set-up is foiled by the jilted Tinhorns, who think they weren’t invited.

episodes.name: Wranglin' Thunderfoot
episodes.overview: Jon wrongly accuses Thunderfoot of scaring their dino herds.

episodes.name: Wings Over Dino Ranch
episodes.overview: When the Tinhorn Trio pick a field of glowing moon lilies, they accidentally prevent a flock of pterosaurs from finding their way home at night.

episodes.name: Bathtime for Bopper
episodes.overview: Clover loves being clean and is eager to help Min bathe the dino mites, but stubborn baby Bopper wants to stay dirty.

episodes.name: Min Flies Solo
episodes.overview: When Maggie the pterosaur hurts her wing, Min needs to copy Jon and Miguel's skills in order to help her.

episodes.name: Tango Dino-Sits
episodes.overview: When Tango is asked to babysit the dino mites, she underestimates how big the job will be.

episodes.name: Fast Friends
episodes.overview: Blitz's patience is tested when he and Jon try to train a fast young raptor.

episodes.name: The Litterhorns
episodes.overview: When Ike Tinhorn decides that it’s easier to dispose of their garbage near Crystal Creek, it spoils the drinking water for dinosaurs downstream.

episodes.name: One Very Special Bronto
episodes.overview: When Clover tries to be the Ranch's protector like Biscuit, he fails to notice that a T-Rex needs his help.

episodes.name: Dino Ranchers- Roll!
episodes.overview: When a T-Rex needs to be rescued, Miguel is confident that his untested new Dino Rumbler is up to the task, but Jon and Min are worried that it isn't ready to take on a real dino rescue.

episodes.name: Risk it for Biscuit
episodes.overview: Out on a mission together, Jon is so keen to impress Biscuit that he causes problems by jumping too quickly into the lead rather than listening and working as a team.

episodes.name: Dino-SOAR!
episodes.overview: When the Jr Ranchers attend the Dino Port's Flyer and Rescue training school their skills are soon called upon to respond to a real rescue!

episodes.name: The Flyer and Rescue Squad
episodes.overview: When Stormwing’s arrival causes trouble for the Dino Port, the fledgling Flyer and Rescue Squad take to the sky to complete their first important mission.

episodes.name: Winging It
episodes.overview: The Jr Ranchers create a prosthetic for a baby pterosaur with a tiny wing, and help her learn how to fly.

episodes.name: Eggs On The Edge
episodes.overview: While trying to save pterosaur eggs during a windstorm, a damaged Dino Buggy complicates things for the Flyer and Rescue Squad.

episodes.name: Rockslide Ravine
episodes.overview: The Rescue Flyers rally to do a seemingly impossible rescue with the help of their whole family.

episodes.name: Flying Colors
episodes.overview: When Jon’s pursuit of his stolen Rescue Flyer Badge puts his family into trouble, Jon chooses to save something more important to him than an award.

episodes.name: The Mighty Dino Mites
episodes.overview: When Blitz’s favorite stuffy goes missing, the dino mites team up to track down the culprit and save the day.

episodes.name: Home Sweet Home
episodes.overview: When Clover tries to help a wild Rhinorex by bringing her home with him, the lovably messy dinosaur soon causes problems for her new Dino Ranch friends.

episodes.name: The Creepy Cryosaur
episodes.overview: When Clara Tinhorn tries to scare the Jr Ranchers during their pumpkin patch harvest, she gets a taste of her own medicine.

episodes.name: Jon's Dino Detour
episodes.overview: After making a mistake, Jon is so keen on doing a good job that he has trouble seeing that a dinosaur needs his help.

episodes.name: Miguel VS Thunderfoot
episodes.overview: When Thunderfoot keeps knocking down a bridge made to help wild dinosaurs, Miguel realizes that the big spinosaur has a hidden reason for wanting the bridge out of the way.

episodes.name: Light Touch Tango
episodes.overview: When Tango’s usual smash-and-bash approach makes things worse for the day’s chores, with help from Miguel’s singing she learns how to gently save the day!

episodes.name: Perky Finds His Purpose
episodes.overview: When Perky stows away on a mission to find two missing Parasaurs, he complicates things when he tries to help the ranchers herd them home, but proves himself in the end.

episodes.name: Raptor Showdown
episodes.overview: Blitz and a pesky microraptor are pitted against one another in a cat and mouse battle of wills, but the tiny dino is a much bigger problem than expected.

episodes.name: Friendship Clashes
episodes.overview: When Min and Clover see Clara and her Raptor not getting along, Min invites them to take part in friendship classes to strengthen their trust, communication, and cooperation skills.

episodes.name: Tango Takes Charge
episodes.overview: When plowing a new field doesn’t go as he wanted, Angus learns that even a stubborn ol’ Tritops like himself can learn something new.

episodes.name: A Dino-Might Night
episodes.overview: When Sonny the Kid tries to steal the Cassidy Christmas Tree, he makes amends by helping them save the day - and is rewarded with a Christmas wish come true.

episodes.name: Luna Sees the Light
episodes.overview: When the Dino Ranchers use lights to communicate with a deaf Parasaur, the baby dino uses them to guide her herd to safety in a snowstorm.

episodes.name: Sonny Daze
episodes.overview: Sonny the Kid gets under Jon’s skin when he cheats during a dino tournament.

episodes.name: Rebel's Wonderful Way
episodes.overview: When Blitz tries to teach Rebel how to be Dino Rancher, he mistakenly pushes his little student to do things his way and puts Rebel into trouble.

episodes.name: Thunderin' Thundertot
episodes.overview: When Clara Tinhorn takes shortcuts on a Dino Ranch practice course, she lands her brothers in trouble and needs to put those skills to use.

episodes.name: Clara's Shortcut Rut
episodes.overview: When Thundertot crashes Clover and Min’s sleepover in the Hatchery, Clover’s plans for the night are interrupted by the rambunctious baby spinosaur.

episodes.name: Little Brother Blues
episodes.overview: When Miguel and Ogie Tinhorn need to team up to help a baby bronto, the two youngest siblings show that they’re the most heroic when they’re just being themselves.

episodes.name: It Takes Two To Tango
episodes.overview: When Aroo pays a surprise visit to Dino Ranch, Tango has so much fun playing with her triceratops friend that she forgets her promise to help Miguel with their chores.

episodes.name: Birthday Bash-less
episodes.overview: When the Jr Ranchers welcome a wild baby triceratops into Tango’s birthday celebrations, Tango gets frustrated when her big, loud events must be changed for the little dino.

episodes.name: Tickle Trouble
episodes.overview: When Clover brings tickly Tickle Bugs onto Dino Ranch, he tries to solve the problem himself and makes the problem even worse.

episodes.name: A Pond Farewell
episodes.overview: When Flopper the Plesiosaur grows too big for her pond, the Dino Ranchers need to find her a new home, but Jon is having a hard time with his friend moving away.

episodes.name: Tyrannosaurus Wrecks
episodes.overview: The Jr Ranchers face a challenge when trying to get a feisty pair of baby T-Rex’s to listen and learn how to be Dino Ranch dinos.

episodes.name: The Dilo Difference
episodes.overview: Jon wants to help a Dilophosaurus fit in on the Ranch, but he runs into problems when the other dinosaurs are startled by the excitable little dino’s appearance.

episodes.name: The Odd Partners
episodes.overview: When headstrong Blitz and stubborn Clara Tinhorn get lost in the Hidden Forest, the two must work together to escape while avoiding an angry mama T-Rex looking for her baby.

episodes.name: Cautious Clover
episodes.overview: After Min nearly comes to harm during a rescue, Clover becomes overly protective, trying to keep her and the other Ranchers out of danger.

episodes.name: Gentle Giselle
episodes.overview: Min and Clover mistakenly think a big gentle Bronto is clumsy, until they realize they were the ones startling her and causing the chaos.

episodes.name: The Power of Two
episodes.overview: When a trio of Rhinorexes block Miguel and Tango’s way over a bridge, they’ll have to work as a team in a way they’ve never tried before.

episodes.name: Min's Dino Mite Mistake
episodes.overview: On their first visit to the Dino Port, the excited Dino Mites are harder to control than Min anticipated.

episodes.name: Supersauruses-Ride!
episodes.overview: Seeing how amazing Biscuit, Angus, and Quack are individually, the Jr Ranchers plan to put them together as a rescue team, but that proves easier said than done.

episodes.name: A Difficult Dino Doctor Day
episodes.overview: When Thundertot feels sick, Dino Doctors Min and Clover have their work cut out for them when the baby spinosaur refuses to let them examine her.

episodes.name: Clover Takes Over
episodes.overview: When Clover’s overconfidence jeopardizes a medical air mission, the bronto learns to ask for help.

episodes.name: You're More Than Your Roar
episodes.overview: When Biscuit gets a case of roaringitis and some egg-stealing Raptors invade the Ranch, Biscuit goes to ridiculous lengths to restore his roar.

episodes.name: Dino Patient Pileup
episodes.overview: When a large amount of dinos with boo-boos need help at the Hatchery, Min neglects to take the time to show Jon, Miguel, Blitz, and Tango how to help her.

episodes.name: Sonny Wings It
episodes.overview: Min needs to find a cactus to make a soothing ointment for some wild stegos but finds herself competing for it with Sonny the Kid... and Stormwing!

episodes.name: Twister with a Chance of Thundertot
episodes.overview: When the Jr Ranchers attend the Dino Port's Flyer and Rescue training school their skills are soon called upon to respond to a real rescue!

episodes.name: Flight of the Bumbling Ogie
episodes.overview: When Stormwing’s arrival causes trouble for the Dino Port, the fledgling Flyer and Rescue Squad take to the sky to complete their first important mission.

episodes.name: Hankie Comes Out of Her Shell
episodes.overview: The hatching of a shy baby Ankylosaur sends Jon and Blitz into a scramble.

episodes.name: Min's Missing Care Case
episodes.overview: Min's confidence takes a tumble when she loses her Care Case on a Dino Doctor mission.

episodes.name: A Dino Mite Graduation
episodes.overview: The baby Dino Mites aren't ready for Flapsy to move to the Pterosaur Barn.

episodes.name: Eye in the Sky
episodes.overview: Pteddy's resistance to wearing vision-improving goggles jeopardizes the Dino Ranchers.

episodes.name: Clash of the Dinos
episodes.overview: Jon and Miguel pair up to teach two baby dinos how to share food.

episodes.name: Steady As We Go
episodes.overview: On a dinosaur-drive through the mountains, Jon discovers that the dinos are comically slow.

episodes.name: No Nest for the Wicked
episodes.overview: When Stormwing snatches Pteddy's nest, the Dino Ranchers mount a rescue mission.

episodes.name: Clara Winhorn!
episodes.overview: Clara Tinhorn lands herself in trouble when she tries to wrangle an angry dinosaur by herself.

episodes.name: The Sneakasaurus
episodes.overview: When someone's causing mischief on Dino Ranch, Blitz becomes determined to catch them.

episodes.name: Sonny's T-Rex Turmoil
episodes.overview: When Sonny the Kid dino-rustles Beans and Gravy to add to his team, they cause Sonny trouble.

episodes.name: The Bronto Bully
episodes.overview: Clover has a run-in with a mean wild dinosaur who takes his toys!

episodes.name: The Rustler and the Rumbler
episodes.overview: When the Jr Ranchers return a rehabilitated T-Rex to her home, Min doubts her doctoring skills!

episodes.name: The Yeti-Saurus
episodes.overview: The gang investigates a dino up on Blizzard Peak and Miguel's wild imagination spooks him.

episodes.name: Wiggle-Tooth Tango
episodes.overview: When one of Tango's teeth starts to wiggle, she shies away from all the rough things.

episodes.name: A Laughing Matter
episodes.overview: A group of Microraptors make the Jr Ranchers look silly.

episodes.name: Great Minds Think of Ike
episodes.overview: Praise from the Ranchers goes to Ike's head, making one of his silly ideas go too far.

episodes.name: A Grand Ole Tree
episodes.overview: Tango can't bring herself to say goodbye to Old Shady, the oldest tree on Dino Ranch.

episodes.name: A Big Friend for Little Sadie
episodes.overview: The Dino Ranchers try to match their friend Sadie with a dinosaur companion.

episodes.name: The Polka-Dot Parasaur
episodes.overview: When a polka-dot parasaur is born on Dino Ranch, the green parasaur herd is taken aback, and it’s up to Min and Clover to show them that his appearance doesn't make him any different than they are.

episodes.name: Dusty the Digging Dino
episodes.overview: A new type of dino causes some upheaval on Dino Ranch, but Miguel figures out a way for them to coexist.

episodes.name: Some Assembly Required
episodes.overview: When the Dino Ranchers need to put together their new construction vehicles, Miguel shows Jon and Min the most important part of an inventor’s process: making mistakes, and try try again!

episodes.name: Angus's Pride and Joy
episodes.overview: Angus's love for his new Dino Transporter draws the overprotective tritops into comic distractions and causes complications for the Jr Ranchers when they try to fix a bridge.

episodes.name: The Tricera-Trekkers
episodes.overview: When Miguel sticks too closely to the Tricera-Trekker rule book, he gets the Tricera-Trekkers in trouble on their special training day.

episodes.name: Flapsy Takes Off
episodes.overview: When Miguel takes on teaching Flapsy to fly, he teaches her using other flying methods, but Flapsy the quetzal wants to try something new!

episodes.name: Grounded!
episodes.overview: When Min and Cloud get sick on the day of Tara’s birthday party, they don’t want to miss out on the fun and try pushing themselves to get better.

episodes.name: Try, Fly Again
episodes.overview: When baby pterosaur Comet struggles to learn how to fly safely after a mishap, Jon tries to encourage her to try again while struggling to overcome an embarrassment of his own.

episodes.name: The Dino Mountaineers
episodes.overview: While using their construction vehicles to help the Mountaineers build the Dino Mountain Outpost, the Jr Ranchers show their neighbors the right way to work with dinosaurs.

episodes.name: Trouble on Dino Mountain
episodes.overview: When the Jr Ranchers discover Kraggletooth causing a ruckus inside the Mountaineers home, they're surprised to learn that Dino Mountain is his home too.

episodes.name: On the Right Track
episodes.overview: Jon and the Jr Ranchers think Dusty and her dino pals are derailing their efforts to finish the cart tracks.

episodes.name: Jasper's Bright Idea
episodes.overview: Jon and Jasper get into trouble when they try to snag a gigantic gem.

episodes.name: Amelia's Empty Nest
episodes.overview: The Dino Ranchers go egg-sitting for an injured pterodactyl

episodes.name: Mountain Mission Accomplished
episodes.overview: an oddly behaving Kraggletooth threatens to spoil the plans for the grand opening of Dino Mountain.

episodes.name: Rock-a-Bye Jasper
episodes.overview: Jasper's love for geodes makes a mess for the Dino Ranchers, plus gets him mistaken for a wild Ankylosaur baby!

episodes.name: The Best Cure of All
episodes.overview: When a baby Stego is sad to be away from his sick Mama, the Jr Ranchers do everything they can to cheer him up.

episodes.name: Beans Go Better With Gravy
episodes.overview: A rambunctious Beans and Gravy make trouble for the Ranchers during a logging chore.

episodes.name: Tango's Barn Raising Ruckus
episodes.overview: Tango soon discovers that they need everyone's help to raise the barn.

episodes.name: Easy as Pie
episodes.overview: When Nibbles the microraptor attempts to steal Pa's birthday pies, the Ranchers think it's Tango who's taking them.

episodes.name: Sticking Together
episodes.overview: when Min and Ike are stuck together, it takes all of Min's gumption to break Ike out of his unhelpful ways to save his siblings.

episodes.name: Good Ol' Goliath
episodes.overview: Clover sabotages the Rumbler, so his tired old grandpa Goliath will have to get into the dinoaction.

episodes.name: Quack's Nest of Friends
episodes.overview: Min and Jane misinterpret Quack's actions when he finds a parasaur nest.

episodes.name: The Battle for Dino Mountain
episodes.overview: When a battle between Kraggletooth and Stormwing causes trouble on Dino Mountain, the Dino Ranchers need to act fast to calm them down.

episodes.name: Danger on Sprial Summit
episodes.overview: After discovering a T-Rex family stuck at the top of Spiral Summit, the Cassidy family must work together to bring the massive wild dinos down the mountain to safety.

episodes.name: Blue Ribbon Ma
episodes.overview: While trying to be like the elite Blue Ribbon Rider, Jon falls into trouble out on a Dino Doctor mission with his Ma - but she has a few elite skills of her own to help him out.

episodes.name: Catch a Comet
episodes.overview: When Wilbur’s baby, Comet, rockets off to explore the tunnels inside Dino Mountain, it’s up to Min, Sadie and Tara to combine their strengths to rescue the playful little pterosaur.

episodes.name: Tough at the Top
episodes.overview: When all of the pterosaurs are afflicted with Wacky Wing Fever, it’s up to Jon and Blitz to save the day by racing to Blizzard Peak for the cure.

episodes.name: Ride 'Em Rancher
episodes.overview: When Jon, Miguel and Min decide to try riding each others' pteros, Thunderbolt and Miguel discover that getting used to a new flyin' partner is easier said than done.

episodes.name: An Unlikely Pair
episodes.overview: When Angus' horns get itchy, he gets so cranky that nobody can get near him -- except for one unlikely friend.

episodes.name: Jon's Speed Limit
episodes.overview: when Jon has trouble keeping up with the speed of a trio of wild raptors, he needs to learn to work within his limits.

episodes.name: Dino Mixup Mayhem
episodes.overview: Miguel feeds the small Dino Ranch Compys some wild bronto berries and sets off a chain reaction that leads to huge consequences,

episodes.name: Sonny's Pterosaur Standoff
episodes.overview: a pterosaur baby takes over Sonny's hideout, the Dino Ranchers must team up with Sonny the kid to help him.
